  "prompt": "When a parking sign says 2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday, what does it mean for the remainder of the time?",
  "response": "When a parking sign indicates \"2-hour parking from 8 to 5 on Monday-Friday,\" it typically means that during those specified hours, you are allowed to park for a maximum of 2 hours. Outside of those hours\u2014after 5 PM on weekdays and all day on weekends and holidays\u2014there are usually no parking restrictions. This means you can park for longer than 2 hours or potentially park for free, but it's always good to double-check for any other signs or regulations that may apply in the area.",
